cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.PF, cs.CE 

The paper deals with the problem of stabilizing voltages in DC microgrids, which involves control theory and power systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the interconnection of Distributed Generation Units (DGUs) and power lines, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of simulations in PSCAD, which is a software for power systems analysis, and hence, the paper could also be classified under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The paper also discusses the use of Linear Matrix Inequality (LMI) problems for local control design, which falls under the category of cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper discusses the use of graph Laplacians for stability analysis, which could be classified under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
